869\"');\r\n\r\n} \r\n\r\ndocument.write('<scr' + 'ipt ' + aScriptAttributes.join(\" \") + '></scr' + 'ipt>'); \r\n</script> \n<p><strong>Sautéd Apple and Cinnamon Oatmeal</strong><br>\n½ cup rolled oats<br>\n1 cup water<br>\n1 apple, diced<br>\n2 tsp cinnamon<br>\n1 tbsp maple syrup<br>\n1 tbsp butter<br>\nChia seeds</p>\n<p>In a small pot, bring 1 cup of water and ½ cup rolled oats to a boil. Once boiling, reduce to a simmer and cover until the oats absorb all of the liquid. Melt the butter in a pan and sauté the diced apples over medium heat until soft. Stir in the maple syrup and cinnamon to the oatmeal and transfer to a bowl. Top with cooked apples and chia seeds.</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_85599\" style=\"width: 970px\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-85599\" data-attachment-id=\"85599\" data-permalink=\"https://dailynexus.com/2019-01-17/three-oatmeal-recipes-to-warm-your-freezing-soul/oatmeal-organic-berry-granola-diet-healthy-muesli/\" data-orig-file=\"https://i1.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Oatmeal-Organic-Berry-Granola-Diet-Healthy-Muesli-3440204.jpg?fit=960%2C638&amp;ssl=1\" data-orig-size=\"960,638\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta='{\"aperture\":\"0\",\"credit\":\"\",\"camera\":\"\",\"caption\":\"\",\"created_timestamp\":\"0\",\"copyright\":\"\",\"focal_length\":\"0\",\"iso\":\"0\",\"shutter_speed\":\"0\",\"title\":\"\",\"orientation\":\"0\"}' data-image-title=\"Oatmeal Organic Berry Granola Diet Healthy Muesli\" data-image-description=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https://i1.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Oatmeal-Organic-Berry-Granola-Diet-Healthy-Muesli-3440204.jpg?fit=250%2C166&amp;ssl=1\" data-large-file=\"https://i1.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Oatmeal-Organic-Berry-Granola-Diet-Healthy-Muesli-3440204.jpg?fit=888%2C590&amp;ssl=1\" class=\"size-full wp-image-85599\" src=\"https://i1.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Oatmeal-Organic-Berry-Granola-Diet-Healthy-Muesli-3440204.jpg?resize=888%2C590\" alt=\"\" width=\"888\" height=\"590\" srcset=\"https://i1.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Oatmeal-Organic-Berry-Granola-Diet-Healthy-Muesli-3440204.jpg?w=960&amp;ssl=1 960w, https://i1.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Oatmeal-Organic-Berry-Granola-Diet-Healthy-Muesli-3440204.jpg?resize=250%2C166&amp;ssl=1 250w, https://i1.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Oatmeal-Organic-Berry-Granola-Diet-Healthy-Muesli-3440204.jpg?resize=768%2C510&amp;ssl=1 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 888px) 100vw, 888px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\"><p id=\"caption-attachment-85599\" class=\"wp-caption-text\"><em>Courtesy of maxpixel.net</em></p></div>\n<p><strong>Steel Cut Oats with Berry Compote</strong><br>\n½ cup steel cut oats<br>\n1½ cup water<br>\n2 tsp lemon juice<br>\n1 tbsp honey<br>\nHandful blueberries<br>\nHandful blackberries<br>\nChia seeds</p>\n<p>In a small pot, bring 1½ cup water and ½ cup steel cut oats to a boil, then reduce to a simmer and cover until all the liquid is absorbed. In a saucepan, cook lemon juice, honey and berries over medium heat until they have reduced down to a jam-like consistency. Pour berry compote over oats and top with chia seeds.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Tips:</strong><br>\nIf you want your oatmeal a bit richer, make it with ½ cup water and ½ cup milk. Also, you’ll want to make sure you turn the temperature pretty low while you’re cooking the oats, they’ll turn out far better than if you blast them on a high temperature.</p>\n<p>All three of these takes on oatmeal are perfect for gloomy mornings. Not only will they keep you nice and warm, but they’ll provide you with the perfect amount of energy to make it through these cold and dreary Winter Quarter days.</p><div class=\"h5ab-print-button-container\"><div class=\"h5ab-print-button h5ab-print-button-left\" style=\"cursor: pointer; color: #555\"><i class=\"fa fa-print fa-lg\"></i>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<